      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Another ER visit might be a hassle, but it's still better to be safe than sorry. Even if you've had this feeling before and it's resolved with antacids, the dull ache in your left arm doesn't rule out more serious conditions like a costochondritis (inflammation of the cartilage that connects the ribs to the breastbone). Given your symptoms and concerns, waiting to see how you feel in an hour may not be the best approach, as you risk missing a potential actual heart issue. If you're really concerned, consider scheduling a same-day doctor's appointment or urgent care visit instead.",
      "source": "target",
